repulsion drives the initial expansion and explains why inflation was
kinetically necessary without invoking an inflaton field.
The quantitative derivation of the expansion rate from the CP/GP density
ratio is deferred to the cosmology companion.

\textbf{(5) Cosmological constant.}  The residual SSV of the DP sea in
the absence of matter is a candidate for the cosmological constant.
Its magnitude in CPP terms is $\Lambda \sim |\SSV|_{\rm abs,\,vacuum}/c^2$,
where $|\SSV|_{\rm abs,\,vacuum}$ is the background ZBW energy density of
the equilibrium DP sea.

\textbf{(6) qDP chaining and strong force.}  The strong-force substrate
(qDP chains between unpaired qCPs, analogous to gluon confinement)
follows the same ZDC chaining mechanism and is treated in a dedicated
companion.

